Bring a large #pot of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry all produce. Trim and
thinly slice @scallions{4%unit}, separating whites from greens. Zest 1 TBSP zest
from @lemons{2%unit} for juice; quarter lemons. Trim ends from @zucchini{2%unit}.
Using a #peeler, shave zucchini lengthwise into ribbons, rotating until you get
to the seedy core; discard core.

Rinse and pat @shrimp{20%ounce} dry with #paper towels. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{4%teaspoon} in a large #pan over
medium-high heat (use a #nonstick pan{} if you have one). Add shrimp and cook,
stirring, until pink and firm, ~{3-5%minutes}. Turn off heat; remove from pan
and set aside. Wipe out pan with a #paper towel.

Heat @butter{2%tablespoon} and a large drizzle of olive oil in same pan over
medium heat. Add scallion whites and cook, stirring, until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}.
Add @cream cheese{4%tablespoon} and @sour cream{4%tablespoon}; reduce heat to
low. Cook, stirring, until smooth, ~{1%minute}. Turn off heat.

Add @lobster ravioli{18%ounce} to #pot of boiling water and reduce heat to low.
Cook until ravioli are tender and float to the top, ~{2-5%minutes}. Scoop out and
reserve 2 cups cooking water, then gently drain ravioli.

Add zucchini ribbons, shrimp, ⅔ cup cooking water, @butter{2%tablespoon}, and
juice from 2 lemon wedges to pan with sauce. Cook on low heat, stirring, until
zucchini is tender, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add ravioli and another @butter{2%tablespoon}.
Stir until thoroughly combined and butter has melted, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> TIP: If pan seems dry, gradually add more cooking water until a creamy sauce
> forms.

Season with salt and pepper.

Divide ravioli between #plates{}. Sprinkle with @Parmesan cheese{1/2%cup},
@lemon zest{1%tablespoon}, scallion greens, and a pinch of @chili flakes{1%teaspoon}.
Serve with remaining lemon wedges for squeezing over.